Text:
Well then, let's hear your report. Were there any
serious issues?
N-No...
Nothing of the sort.
Well then, what's with the long faces?
Well, you see...

...We've compiled a report on Annerose Nichtsehen's
activities over the past week.
Please take a look at this first.

Oh, you've been doing your job properly. Impressive,
very impressive...
...Hmm?
What the... Huh?
...*sigh*
No. 111 and No. 122. Let me just confirm one thing.

Is everything in this report about Annerose's
activities true?
Everything...is absolutely true.
It's shocking, but it's true.
Huhhh...?
...Neither of you knew Annerose personally, did you?

I knew of her as one of the empire's most renowned
sword fighters, but I had never personally met her.

Same for me. Even as a former instructor, I never
interacted with her.
Then, this report is free of any personal biases.
...I see...
So, this swordswoman, Annerose Nichtsehen, is...
Upright! And extremely naive!

In other words...she's completely oblivious to the
position she's in.
Yes.
Indeed...

...While you were discreetly observing her, she was
attacked by a mysterious group on four occasions.

All the assailants were Cult members under Sergey,
and Annerose fended them off on her own... She's
remarkably skilled.

Furthermore, despite such circumstances, she
continues to naively and steadfastly seek the
truth behind what happened to Lady Karen.

...No. 111, how would you assess Annerose's sword
skills?

She may not be superior to Sergey, but she's nearly
on par with him.

If not for Sergey's regenerative abilities, she could
likely hold her own against him, depending on the
circumstances.
I have to ask, who's stronger between you and her?

...If she wields a sword, and I a spear in an open
space without obstacles, we would be almost evenly
matched.

So you're admitting that she's stronger than you,
Miss Former Baroness.
Mnhh...!
No. 122, refrain from unnecessary personal jibes.

...Anyway, despite Annerose's strength, her actions
are too straightforward.

She's genuinely seeking the truth about what happened
between the Herzog Family and Lady Karen without any
suspicion of conspiracy...

Though they are in the minority, some in Vegalta
object to her inheriting the title of one of Vegalta's
Seven Blades.

While some heartlessly insinuate her involvement in
Lady Karen's disappearance, Annerose herself appears
unfazed.

She's honestly investigating the incident as a knight
of the empire. Simply put, she's a national treasure
of a swordswoman, too virtuous and stupid for her
own good.
No. 122, careful with how you phrase things!
But it's the truth.

No. 122 might have hit the mark with that
description. How else could Annerose run her
investigation so openly and defenselessly?

While she relentlessly pursues the truth, she's faced
multiple attacks yet has repelled all assailants.

Considering her prominent status as one of the new
Seven Blades, the Cult likely can't go all out to
assassinate her...

Also, being one of the Seven Blades means she is
always on high alert for threats. This vigilance
leaves little opportunity for the Cult to make a move.

In other words, her virtues as a swordswoman draw
danger her way, but paradoxically, those very virtues
shield her.

Consequently, the Cult can't deal her a decisive
blow. Instead, they continuously squander their
resources on futile attempts.

It's a miraculous balance of crisis evasion. The only
one oblivious to this is Annerose Nichtsehen herself.

Until either Sergey, one of the Seven Blades, or the
Children of Diablos step in, this situation will
likely persist...

...As the Garden, we could use Annerose's virtue to
draw out Sergey...

No... Perhaps it's better to actively support her
"visible activities" to create a favorable scenario
for us.

If the Cult finds it too challenging to deal with her
directly, they might try to pin the Lady Karen
incident on Annerose.
Hold on...!
True...!

...In any case, we'll determine our course of action
once we've met her in person.
